  <notes>
  <p>
  Supposedly a Boddington's clone.
  This one worked out OK.  At bottling time, I thought this would be
  one of the best beers I've ever made.  It was hoppy, crisp, with
  some nice apple esters.  When it was conditioned, it was merely OK.
  All the apple esters dissappeared.  To improve it, I'd add some more
  hops in the middle of the boil and use a different yeast.  In
  retrospect, I've come to dislike 1098.
  </p>
